You cannot spend what you do not have.  Even if it's for a noble goal, if you spend too much, and consistently run a deficit, it hurts more people in the longterm and it prevents you later on from providing needed programs.  It's an unfortunate fact of life, but we must as a society learn to be fiscally responsible.<br>
