<br>
I'd like to see the system improved upon and more people covered.  It's not really 40 million that are the problem, many of those choose not to have health insurance (my sister for example, who would rather keep the money than buy insurance, even though she could afford it.  I respect her right to make that decision.)  I'd also like people to have the option of taking the voucher in cash and forgoing medical insurance.  This would ensure anyone *can* have medical insurance, but allow people who do not wish to have that insurance to take their part in cash for whatever purposes they choose.  This option should not be available to children or people not of sound mind.<br>
<br>
The problem right now is we cannot afford such a program.  The approximate cost is somewhere between 250 and 300 billion dollars per year.  We need to pay off our national debt first.  This is what I mean when I say above that it is bad to spend what we do not have.  It just creates problems later, now we cannot afford to provide health care because we already spent that money a long time ago.<br>
